snippet.textDisplay: A match that none of the teams deserved to lose. They both played nice attacking football. I honestly hope both teams will achieve their goals (that is, survival for Samp, and at least Europa League for Napoli). It's a shame that a few Sampdoria fans chanted "Vesuvio, lavali" (that is, "Vesuvio, errupt!"), but come on - those idiots can't be called fans. snippet.textDisplay: With Napoli’s victory over Sampdoria today & the main teams competing for the 4th spot all dropping points, their UCL hopes are no longer a pipe dream!! I don’t see Verona Parma or Cagliari (who are at the moment ahead of Napoli) being a threat this second half of the season, so the only teams we really have to worry about are Roma Milan & Atalanta! We play the first 2 at home & a crucial away fixture at Bergamo which I honestly don’t think we’ll lose! With Napoli’s upcoming Serie A fixtures (most being bottom of the half teams) & home advantage over the main 4th spot competitors, plus Koulibaly & Mertens back & most importantly OUR FORM, NAPOLI CAN DEFINITELY MAKE 4TH PLACE THIS SEASON!!!
